I"Ä<h2 id="solution">Solution:</h2>

<p>Let $P(n)$ be a polynomial in $n$ of degree $k$. That is,</p>

\[P(n) = a_kn^k + a_{k - 1}n^{k - 1} + \cdots + a_1n + a_0\]

<p>where $k \in \mathbb{N}$ and $a_i \in \mathbb{R}$ for $i = 0, 1, 2, \ldots, k$. Also, let</p>

\[Q(n) = \left[1 + \left( \sum_{i = 0}^{k} a_i \right) \right] n^{k!}\]

<p>Clearly, $P(n) \leq Q(n)$ for all $n \geq 1$. Hence, $log_b(P(n)) \leq log_b(Q(n))$ for all $b \in \mathbb{Z+}$</p>
